Measurement Bias Analysis of EGMA number recognition at Endline by Gender in Malawi

PFH & KKN

August 26, 2020

  • Summary
    • Robustness Checks for Treatment Effects Conditional on Comparison Variable
  • Bias Detection Methods
    • Graphical Analyis via Loess
    • Mantel-Haenszel
    • Logistic Regression
    • Item Response Theory

Summary

Dataset: Malawi

Outcome variable: EGMA number recognition at Endline (recog1 - recog20)

Comparison variable: Gender (Male, Female)

Items with no variance:a none

Items with no variance within levels of comparison variable:b none

Bias detection method: IRT

Total number of biased items: 2 out of 20

Type of item bias: non-uniform

a Items were not included in any DIF analysis and were not used to compute IRT-based robustness checks of treatment effects.

b Items were not included in the IRT-based DIF analysis and were not used to compute IRT-based robustness checks of treatment effects.
